1.title: From Before to After
1.plot: Following a STYLEHAUL event, Fiona (LISA KUDROW) discovers she's won a fashion makeover with Nina Garcia (HERSELF), creative director of Marie Claire magazine.

2.title: Replacement Gifts
2.plot: Caspar Lee (HIMSELF) calls to revoke Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) auction-won makeover with Nina Garcia, and offer her anything else instead.

3.title: Ladrona! Ladrona! Fiona!
3.plot: Nina Garcia (HERSELF), against her better judgment, proceeds with Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) makeover, but is surprised by the fallout of that decision.

4.title: Internetainment
4.plot: Caspar Lee (HIMSELF) calls with a very different proposal from last time, but Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) desire to diagnose and impose her therapy gets in the way.

5.title: Call Me Dad
5.plot: Garreth Pink (BILLY CRYSTAL) calls to complain about his new wife, Fiona's mother.

6.title: Marriage Sack
6.plot: Having followed Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) marriage counseling, Garreth (BILLY CRYSTAL) calls back with some good and bad news.

7.title: He Liked You Too Much
7.plot: Putsy (LILY TOMLIN) explains her recent marital woes to Fiona (LISA KUDROW).

8.title: Betsy Boss
8.plot: Putsy (LILY TOMLIN) prepares to "get in deep" with the governor during a Revolutionary War reenactment.

9.title: We've Been Played
9.plot: Hayley (RASHIDA JONES) has returned from Bali with renewed spiritual purpose, and attempts to make amends with Fiona (LISA KUDROW).

10.title: Baby Bumps
10.plot: Fiona (LISA KUDROW) and Hayley (RASHIDA JONES) gang up on deceitful Jerome (DAN BUCATINSKY), but Fiona has an ace up her sleeve.

11.title: Pump the Brakes
11.plot: Putsy (LILY TOMLIN) realizes the only way to win a Supreme Court appointment is to "manufacture a vacancy" on the Bench.

12.title: Burdensome Gifts
12.plot: Fiona (LISA KUDROW) is shocked to discover the NYC penthouse she received as a gift comes with very expensive strings.

13.title: Potty Training
13.plot: Jerome (DAN BUCATINSKY) is taking full advantage of Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) NYC penthouse, hopefully benefiting Fiona's bottom line.

14.title: Penthouse Problems
14.plot: Fiona (LISA KUDROW) is on the hook for the penthouse expenses when Jerome (DAN BUCATINSKY) admits it wasn't as luxurious as he thought it'd be.

15.title: Welcome Wagoner
15.plot: Wealthy neighbor Grace Tiverton (LAUREN GRAHAM) invites Fiona (LISA KUDROW) to join her women's group, but what's in it for Fiona?

16.title: Neighbor/Nuisance
16.plot: Following the poorly attended neighborhood game night, Fiona (LISA KUDROW) is suspicious of how well Grace (LAUREN GRAHAM) knows the societal women she claims to know.

17.title: Cunning Chameleon
17.plot: Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) attempt at an apology backfires when Grace (LAUREN GRAHAM) reveals the changed circumstances in the 'hood.

18.title: Together But Apart
18.plot: Fiona (LISA KUDROW) and Kip (VICTOR GARBER) rekindle their relationship and admit that it's better when they're not together.

19.title: Attachment Issues
19.plot: Kip's law clerk, April, goes above and beyond - maybe even too far - to satisfy his every need. Is Fiona in trouble?

20.title: Out in the Open
20.plot: April's (CALISTA FLOCKHART) assistance is a dream come true for Fiona (LISA KUDROW) - well, except for her not-so-secret love for Fiona's husband, Kip (VICTOR GARBER).

21.title: All About April
21.plot: April (CALISTA FLOCKHART) works her way towards being the new Mrs. Kip Wallice, and is Fiona (LISA KUDROW) even upset?

22.title: Absolute Last Call
22.plot: Fiona takes on a new client who is only interested in older women - much older.

23.title: Dropping Candy Bars
23.plot: Jeb Masters (JON HAMM) questions his whole existence after meeting Fiona (LISA KUDROW) in person.

24.title: Jeb Therapy
24.plot: Jeb (JON HAMM) is relieved when he discovers Fiona (LISA KUDROW) is wiser and more wizened than he thought.

25.title: Executor
25.plot: Austen's brother, Ewan Clarke (CRAIG FERGUSON), calls to clarify issues regarding the liquidation of Austen's estate.

26.title: Sell Out
26.plot: Ewan (CRAIG FERGUSON) is not responding well to his role as his brother's executor. Can Fiona (LISA KUDROW) "help" him out?

27.title: Net Therapy Redux
27.plot: Ewan's (CRAIG FERGUSON) plan, to declare Austen insane, backfires without Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) testimony, but there's a silver lining that makes it all worthwhile.

28.title: Looking at Other Things
28.plot: Prudish new client Judith Frick (ALLISON JANNEY) asks Fiona (LISA KUDROW) for advice about a rocky relationship with her future son-in-law.

29.title: Learning Experience
29.plot: Judith Frick (ALLISON JANNEY) calls back, having had a much more intimate experience with her future son-in-law than she anticipated.

30.title: Coital Consequences
30.plot: Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) plotting may have backfired, but she inadvertently solves all of Judith's (ALLISON JANNEY) issues. Maybe she is a good therapist?

31.title: State Secrets
31.plot: A long-time admirer (DAX SHEPHARD) calls Fiona (LISA KUDROW) to come clean.

32.title: Terror Threat
32.plot: Admirer-turned-foe, Abel Jans (DAX SHEPHARD), warns Fiona (LISA KUDROW) that she's a terror threat - she only ruins people's lives.

33.title: Surprising Results
33.plot: Fiona's (LISA KUDROW) advice surprisingly hits home with Abel (DAX SHEPHARD), so he's turning over a new leaf, and Fiona's off the hook.

1.title: An Old Flame: Part 1
1.plot: Fiona is surprised when her new client turns out to be Richard, a fondly-remembered old flame.

2.title: An Old Flame: Part 2
2.plot: Fiona is more seductive then professional when Richard brings up his new girlfriend, Sheila.

3.title: An Old Flame: Part 3
3.plot: Fiona is flattered when Richard make s personal breakthrough.

4.title: Sibling Ribaldry: Part 1
4.plot: Fiona wants to terminate her dullest patient, Jerome- until he reveals a sensational and, for Fiona, a potentially profitable family secret.

5.title: Sibling Ribaldry: Part 2
5.plot: Fiona meets with Jerome and his girlfriend, Hayley, to explore their "relationship"- and how it can best serve Fiona's practice.

6.title: Sibling Ribaldry: Part 3
6.plot: When Jerome's promotable back story turns out to be false- and thereby useless to Fiona- the stressed out therapist hits the roof.

7.title: The Breakthrough: Part 1
7.plot: Fiona accuses her new client Ted Mtchell of being overly judgmental- until she learns about the real reason he sought her out for treatment.

8.title: The Breakthrough: 2 of 3
8.plot: Fiona practices her "groundbreaking technique" on Ted - and the results are spectacular.

9.title: The Breakthrough: 3 of 3
9.plot: For Ted, its a psychological breakthrough. For Fiona, its just another way to grow her practice.

10.title: Psycho Analysis: Part 1
10.plot: Fiona's new client is a high strung business woman who does not even have three minutes to spare.

11.title: Psycho Analysis: Part 2
11.plot: Fiona's latest advice could cost Claire's job - and Fionas safety and wellbeing.

12.title: Psycho Analysis: Part 3
12.plot: Despite her best efforts, Fiona finds her self in another session with Claire, who she may now be seeing for a long time.

13.title: Exposing the Truth: Part 1
13.plot: Fiona meets, Bryn, a young successful woman whose boyfriend, Justin, doesn't seem to appreciate all of her hard work.

14.title: Exposing the Truth: Part 2
14.plot: If Bryn's career wasn't enough, Justin reveals something about his childhood that makes Fiona want to clear her schedule.

15.title: Exposing the Truth: Part 3
15.plot: Fiona discovers Bryn and Justin's real motives for going to her. And she is not happy.

1.title: Gossip Girl: Part 1
1.plot: Fiona is put off by a new client, Robin, a self-diagnosed exercise bulimic. Fiona tries to rattle Robin with a barrage psychological attacks-until Robin reveals her true relationship with Fiona's husband. Robin ends the sessions with an unexpected bombshell.

2.title: Gossip Girl: Part 2
2.plot: Fiona, perturbed by Robin's disclosure, tries to rattle her with a barrage of psychological attacks -- until Robin counters by revealing her true relationship with Fiona's husband.

3.title: Gossip Girl: Part 3
3.plot: Robin, heartbroken after her plans have backfired, drops an unexpected bombshell on Fiona.

4.title: Office Politics: Part 1
4.plot: Fiona continues to be bored by the relationship issues of her longtime client, Jerome, until she stumbles upon a way to use him in her marital battle.

5.title: Office Politics: Part 2
5.plot: Jerome, having taken Fiona's advice to heart, has landed himself in hot water with his company-and Fiona has to duck for cover.

6.title: Office Politics: Part 3
6.plot: Jerome thanks Fioan for finding a new position, but his new complaints of his new job leaves Fiona cold.

7.title: Psychic Friends: Part 1
7.plot: Serena claims that Fiona has cured her. In return, Fiona sees a chance to get national attention.

8.title: Psychic Friends: Part 2
8.plot: Serena claims that Fiona has cured her. In return, Fiona sees a chance to get national attention.

9.title: Psychic Friends: Part 3
9.plot: A tumultuous meeting in person behind them, Fiona and Serena part ways -- but not before Serena delivers one more prophecy.

10.title: Kiss and Tell: Part 1
10.plot: Fiona is shocked when her former employer and current investor, Robert Lachman, logs on to get her to help her with a rare compulsive disorder.

11.title: Kiss and Tell: Part 2
11.plot: Fiona agrees to help Robert, suddenly the most infamous swindler, but this drowning man almost submerges his recover.

12.title: Kiss and Tell: Part 3
12.plot: Fiona succeeds in benefiting from her association with Robert, but in a surprising way that leaves him furious and Fiona well on the way to being famous.

13.title: Flying High: Part 1
13.plot: Fiona finds the perfect client in Austen Clarke, the Scottish media mogul, and he's every bit as delighted with her.

14.title: Flying High: Part 2
14.plot: As luck would have it, Austen is perfectly situated to help Fiona with her latest venture and she "reluctantly" agrees to let him put her on the map.

15.title: Flying High: Part 3
15.plot: Fiona is flying high with Austen-- but an unexpected call from her husband could bring her right back to earth.

17.title: Healing Touch
17.plot: Fiona is eager to join Kip in his recovery, but discovers that his treatment with Camilla has progressed quickly, and alarmingly, beyond the usual talk and aversion therapy.

18.title: Reverse Psychology
18.plot: Fiona gives Camilla a hands-on demonstration of the effectiveness, or otherwise, of Camilla's therapeutic techniques when she arranges a meeting with Camilla's husband.

1.title: Morals to the Max
1.plot: Fiona gets an earful from her publisher's chief of staff, Maxine DeMaine, who has a very low opinion of Fiona's writing skills - and her moral character.

2.title: I Heart New York
2.plot: Behind Fiona's back, Jerome flies up to New York to meet with Maxine to fix her book, but doesn't get the thanks he expects.

3.title: Tokens of Affection
3.plot: Baffled by the modest trickle of gifts from Austen, Fiona decides to take her affection - and book - elsewhere.

4.title: Publishers Cleaning House
4.plot: Fiona is outfoxed by the calculating Maxine, but the book is back where it belongs - and so is Austen.

5.title: The Host Whisperer
5.plot: Conan O'Brien contacts Fiona for help with unexpressed anger... but manages to express plenty when she fails to recognize him.

6.title: Quid Pro Conan
6.plot: Conan reaches across the country to help Fiona with a problem with her neighbor -- and expects a favor in return.

7.title: Guess Who's Coming to Late Night
7.plot: After his revenge plan backfires, Conan learns that when it comes to Fiona, feelings should be swallowed, not expressed.

8.title: The Royal Treatment
8.plot: Fiona gets her first international client when Gemma Pankhurst-Jones (NATASHA BEDINGFIELD) calls from Buckingham Palace, where she works as a "proxy" for the royal family. When she says her recent marriage remains unconsummated, Fiona concludes this is therapy by proxy -- and the new royal marriage is in trouble!

9.title: Speed Bump
9.plot: Fiona's conjugal advice is unsuccessful, and Gemma says she's running out of time -- she's pregnant, and her husband is bound to know he can't be the father. Can Fiona save the British empire?

10.title: Heir Today, Gone Tomorrow
10.plot: The London tabloids are full of a royal scandal that mysteriously echoes Gemma's situation, and Gemma finally realizes that Fiona's therapy is all talk -- mostly to the press.

11.title: Hooray for Hollywood
11.plot: Fiona thinks she's been discovered by Hollywood when newly sober reality star Allegra Favreau calls to option Fiona's memoir for a Lifetime television movie.

12.title: That's How I Role
12.plot: Allegra Favreau does character research on Fiona, grilling her on some embarrassing details left out of her memoir, and Fiona offers up an acting critique of Allegra's past work before they agree to continue the work face-to-face in L.A.

13.title: Come Fly with Me
13.plot: Jerome surprises Fiona with an unwelcome traveling companion for her trip to Los Angeles.

14.title: Acting Out
14.plot: Fiona and Allegra conduct a postmortem on the disastrous trip to Los Angeles, and Allegra, now a Hollywood pariah based on some unfortunate camera phone footage, prepares for a long stretch on the casting couch.

15.title: Hands-On Therapy
15.plot: Fiona's mother, Putsy Hodge, wants to be declared legally insane, and Fiona, once she finds out why, instantly agrees.

16.title: Cell Phone
16.plot: After her roommate's unfortunate death, Putsy Hodge prepares for life in the Big House, while Fiona begs her to lawyer up and take the Fifth.

17.title: The Family Business
17.plot: Fiona is pleased to discover that Putsy has been cleared of all charges, but horrified when she discovers that Putsy has a new career - and, worse, a new career advisor.

1.title: Broadway Babies
1.plot: Franny Marshall, who is writing the songs for Whistlin', calls Fiona with a case of writer's block.

2.title: Encore, Encore!
2.plot: Fiona calls Franny to share the good news that during a drunken night out on the town, Franny broke through her writer's block.

3.title: Eff Broadway
3.plot: Franny's new songs garner her major attention and propel her into the Pop world.

4.title: Inspired By/Stolen From
4.plot: Jerome tells Fiona the good news: Google wants to buy her mother's copycat therapy business.

5.title: Now You're Talking About My Mother
5.plot: Jerome, no longer in Putsy's good graces, calls Fiona to ask for his job back.

6.title: Rubber Sheets
6.plot: Fiona is infuriated to discover that Hayley has been using her NY Penthouse to entertain.

7.title: Dixie. Pixie. Smiley Face.
7.plot: Desperate for access to the campaign documents, Fiona calls Richard to see if he remembers the pass codes.

8.title: It Might Have Been Ben Tomlund
8.plot: Feigning interest in Robin's "documentary" accomplishments, Fiona calls to get access to her tapes. Desperate for evidence that she's been framed, Fiona feigns interest in Robin's "documentary" accomplishments to get access to her footage.

9.title: Once a Blackmailer...
9.plot: Fiona is horrified to learn that Robin once again has the upper hand - along with incriminating footage of Austen Clarke.

10.title: One Big Russian Family
10.plot: Fiona asks Richard to help her by destroying Robin's damaging tapes.

11.title: Just Say This Word
11.plot: Fiona contacts Richard to give him a heads up that the FBI has been tipped off to his mob employers.

12.title: Witless Protection
12.plot: Richard tries to secretly contact Fiona to let her know that he and Robin will be going into Witness Protection.

13.title: We're in Good with the NRA
13.plot: Kip's call with Fiona is interrupted by Ben, who has some unsettling campaign news.

14.title: You Picked a Winner.
14.plot: Fiona, concerned about how heated the investigation has become, calls Kip desperate for help with accessing his accounts.

15.title: Game, Set Up, Match
15.plot: A smug Fiona gets some satisfaction from Ben's current predicament with the law.

16.title: Rejuvenation
16.plot: Fiona is shocked to find out that Austen plans to marry his baby mama Gina, to secure a legitimate heir.

17.title: Get It Outta Me!!
17.plot: A very pregnant Gina calls Fiona from Austen's Jet to discuss wedding plans.

18.title: Paternity Rites
18.plot: Jerome contacts Gina with an unusual request having to do with her baby.

19.title: The Archivist
19.plot: Fiona introduces herself to Karen Sharpe, the hoarder who is obsessed with Kip, in order to strike a deal for his briefcase.

20.title: You Know How I Love Puzzles
20.plot: Fiona makes her way into Karen's house to try and get her hands on Kip's briefcase, which has the evidence she needs to clear herself.

21.title: Extreme Makeover: Hoarder Edition
21.plot: Karen calls Fiona very upset, having woken up to find herself and her home newly made-over.

22.title: Lucky Charm
22.plot: Fiona gets a call from a new patient Nick Jericho, whose wife says he has a gambling problem.

23.title: Used Cards
23.plot: Nick calls Fiona extremely frustrated that he has lost a lot of money to a crafty new online gambler.

24.title: Deuces Ex Machina
24.plot: Nick discovers that Fiona is the secret card shark who has been beating him online.

25.title: Power Balls
25.plot: New client Steve Olson reaches out to Fiona for help with his anxiety after winning the NY lottery.

26.title: Divestment Opportunities
26.plot: Steve questions Fiona's motives after receiving a proposal to invest in Web Therapy.

27.title: Swindle in the City
27.plot: Fiona is shocked to learn that Steve isn't who he claimed to be.

28.title: Long-Distance Lovers
28.plot: Young couple Blair and Augie reach out for advice from Fiona concerning their long-distance cyber relationship.

29.title: Losing Followers
29.plot: During a session with Blair and Augie, Fiona discovers that the couple is having relationship problems.

30.title: Closer When We're Apart
30.plot: Fiona is stunned to discover that Blair and Augie think they can solve their problems without her.

31.title: Penetratress
31.plot: Fiona becomes reacquainted with her former flame Chris Endicott, who has changed a lot since college.

32.title: Hatching a Plan
32.plot: Chris is desperate: does Fiona want to save a friend's marriage?

33.title: Spritzer Surprise
33.plot: Fiona is upset that Chris suckered her into being taped by reality TV cameras at their dinner.

34.title: Integrate Now
34.plot: New client, Sylvie Frank, seeks Fiona's advice concerning her office romance that has gone sour.

35.title: You've Come a Long Way Baby
35.plot: Fiona is stunned to learn her advice landed Sylvie a lucrative new job.

imdb.title: Web Therapy
plot: Dr. Fiona Wallice is sick of hearing about "dreams" and "feelings". She then decides that 3 minutes over web cam is better than 50 minutes of patients rambling on.::wolfee37
